# Infinite Vision — Deployment & Changes

## When user requests updates
1. Apply Super Master Prompt (content + program model + partners)
2. Modify codebase cleanly with minimal scope
3. Explain what changed
4. Verify `npm run build` still succeeds when changes are substantial
5. Suggest commit message only if user asks to commit

## Deployment workflow
- **Local**: `npm run dev` (default port 3000; use `-p` if occupied)
- **GitHub**: clean history, deploy-ready main branch
- **Vercel**: maintain compatibility; document env vars if added; do not log into Vercel or modify DNS

## Key routes (maintain)
- `/` — homepage
- `/programs`, `/programs/housing-pathways`, `/programs/transportation-access`, `/programs/financial-empowerment`, `/programs/community-integration`
- `/partners`, `/operations`

## Auto-fix when possible
- Imports, routing, component mismatches, accessibility basics (labels, headings, focus, skip link)
- Keep header logo at `public/infinite-vision-logo.png` with accessible home link
